The paper discusses safe reinforcement learning on autonomous vehicles, which involves the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper focuses on using prediction to constrain exploration in reinforcement learning. The second most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics), as the paper specifically applies safe reinforcement learning to autonomous vehicles. The third most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper discusses advances in reinforcement learning and how it can be applied to real-world systems. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper deals with controlling the behavior of autonomous vehicles in a safe and reliable manner. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper may involve using visual information to make decisions about intersection handling.
